NEW498H1-F-20225.courseTitle: Critical and Creative Perspectives on Community Based Research (CBR): An Advanced Seminar
NEW498H1-F-20225.courseDescription: Explores how research is conducted and mobilized by marginalized communities as a form of resistance, knowledge production and social change. Examines the foundations of empirical research, the role of the university as a site of research activity and the ethics and methods of community-based research. Informed by examples of grassroots research projects from Black, Indigenous and racialized communities locally, nationally and globally. In this course, students engage in community-based and participatory action research projects with community partners. Not eligible for CR/NCR option.
NEW498H1-F-20225.prerequisite: Completion of 9.0 credits and successful completion of the application process.
NEW498H1-F-20225.recommendedPreparation: CAR120Y1/ AFR150Y1/ CAR220H1/ CAR221H1/ NEW224Y1/ CAR225H1/ CAR226H1/ BPM232H1/ NEW232Y1/ NEW240Y1/ CSE241Y1/ CSE270H1/ HIS230H1/ HIS231H1/ other New College courses
NEW498H1-F-20225.webTimetableInstructions: Enrolment is via application. Please see the Community Engaged Learning website for more information: http://www.newcollege.utoronto.ca/academics/new-college-academic-programs/community-engaged-learning/
